How and Why we Classify?
Classification is a universal mental act that we all perform.
A lot of classification is personal (e.g., music we like, don’t like; food we like, don’t like; people, etc.)

How and Why we Classify?
Classification is a universal mental act that we all perform.
A lot of classification is personal (e.g., music we like, don’t like; food we like, don’t like; people, etc.)
We cut up the world into personal islands of meaning.
Classification is a process of sculling up these islands rather than identifying something that already exists in the natural world.
Breaking up the world into mental chunks is accomplished through language.
